snippet.textDisplay:
A good attempt to bring Uttarakhand’s culture to the main stage. Congratulations to the team and Kamla Devi Ji. Overall presentation and setting of the music theme is also commendable.

However, any deviations and  modifications done to the soul or genesis of the song is not acceptable.
No ‘Jagar/Cultural song’ requires any modern instruments. It feels good only when it is sung with traditional instruments like Dhol, Damau, Hudka (in this case). 

Once Sonu Nigam Sir said, when you are singing a cultural song, the first thing is to understand the singing style and the nuances behind it. Merely singing it is not enough, you should inculcate those styles into your singing as well.

Apart from Kamla Devi ji part of singing, the rest of the song seems arbitrary and doesn’t makes any sense.

Appreciating the efforts, but we should not promote any such remixes which plays with the overall sentiment of the song.
